WEBVTT

00:00:05.960 --> 00:00:10.680
It is advisable to overlock the raw edge
at the lower part of the shoulder seam.

00:00:12.080 --> 00:00:15.760
Fold the lower edge of the
shoulder pad fabric 1 centimetre.

00:00:19.240 --> 00:00:23.400
Stitch along the seam allowance at
1-centimetre intervals,

00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:25.280
4mm in from the raw edge.

00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:54.480
Place the two shoulder
pads right sides together.

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:02.720
Place a pin at the centre of the length.

00:01:07.960 --> 00:01:09.360
Fold it in half.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:15.120
Place cardboard between the shoulder pads.

00:01:16.480 --> 00:01:18.560
The collar opening is indicated.

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:22.960
2cm further back towards the
back panel than Katayama.

00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:27.200
As shown in the table,
insert 8.6 cm scissors.

00:01:38.880 --> 00:01:42.560
Pin the seam allowance on
the back piece in place.

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:50.400
Mark a 1-centimetre point.

00:02:08.360 --> 00:02:09.520
Carving technique. The feel of the wood.

00:02:09.640 --> 00:02:14.400
Leave a 1.6 cm seam allowance at
the back and sew the back seam.

00:02:30.640 --> 00:02:34.560
Sew one stitch along the folded edge
at the lower part of the shoulder pad.

00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:40.440
I shall secure it.

00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:54.560
The collar should be worn with
the open side to the right.

00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:58.000
I'll knock it over with a
2-millimetre gap on the other side.

00:03:04.040 --> 00:03:07.080
Align the body piece towards you and the
shoulder pad piece

00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:08.400
towards the opposite side,

00:03:09.280 --> 00:03:15.800
Align the cut edges of the open collar
and secure the back seam with flat pins.

00:03:27.560 --> 00:03:31.160
Sew with a 2-centimetre stitching
distance, 1 millimetre

00:03:31.160 --> 00:03:32.720
outside the centre seam.

00:03:34.160 --> 00:03:40.040
At this stage, use white lower
thread No. 30 for the binding thread.

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:45.560
The lower part of the
shoulder is stitched twice.

00:03:50.040 --> 00:03:52.680
Sew the two pieces together diagonally.

00:04:01.360 --> 00:04:02.840
I shall secure it.

00:04:09.360 --> 00:04:12.840
Lay the body and shoulder
pads flat with the seams open.

00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:26.480
Align the collar, shoulder, autumn seam
allowance and the edge of the

00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:29.240
front panel, then secure with pins.

00:04:44.520 --> 00:04:49.320
To ensure the collar attachment line is
visible from the shoulder pad side, mark

00:04:49.320 --> 00:04:52.840
the folds using the collar
attachment and lapel drop marks.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:10.320
Pin the area 4 millimetres outside
the collar and shoulder seam.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:33.440
Align the shoulder peak on the sleeve
attachment side and pin it flat.

00:05:40.480 --> 00:05:43.520
Fold the sleeve attachment line in the
same manner as the

00:05:43.520 --> 00:05:44.880
collar and shoulder area.

00:05:51.520 --> 00:05:55.320
Secure the outer edge 4 millimetres
in with basting stitches.
